    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-01T16:03:51+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-01T16:03:51+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T06:33:51Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-01T06:33:51Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A series of low pressure systems passing over waters to the south will extend cold fronts that will cross over SA through to the end of the week. A high pressure system is then forecast to move into the Bight from late Friday and extend a ridge across the state over the weekend, as it slowly moves southeastwards towards Tasmania.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW005" description="Lower South East" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <warning-summary type="sheep_graziers_warning" start-time-local="2026-07-01T10:38:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T01:08:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z">Warning to Sheep Graziers</warning-summary>
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-01T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm early this evening. Winds northerly 20 to 30 km/h turning northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain. The chance of a thunderstorm near the coast. Possible small hail in the late afternoon and evening. Damaging winds possible near the coast. Winds northwesterly 30 to 45 km/h turning westerly during the afternoon and evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching around 13.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 1 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers, most likely in the early morning with possible small hail in the south. Damaging winds possible near the coast. Winds west to southwesterly 35 to 50 km/h decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 7 with daytime temperatures reaching around 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. Winds southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending southerly during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching around 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower in the south, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching around 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
